President of Iran:If the lifting of sanctions against Iraq is expected to reach an agreement-Xinhuanet Xinhua Agency, Tehran, December 11 thif that United States lifts its sanction against Iran, Iran will reach a "good deal" on the comprehensive nuclear agreement (JCPOA), Iran president Mahmoud Leahy said in Tehran on Monday."Iran has proved its sincerity in negotiations by submit proposals to other parties to the JCPOA," he said at a meeting with Iranian envoys to neighboring countries, according to the presidential website."The road to an agreement will be clear." The parties involved in the Iranian nuclear agreement began talks in Vienna, Austria, in April this year to discuss the resumption of compliance between the United States and Iran. A new round of talks began in Vienna on November 29, adjourned on December 3 and continued on December 9.
